{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-1607","published":"2024-05-17T11:08:03Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:08.283573Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-27282"],"summary":"ruby security update","details":"Ruby is a fast and easy interpreted scripting language for object-oriented programming. It has many functions for processing text Files and perform system management tasks (such as Perl).\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nAn issue was discovered in Ruby 3.x through 3.3.0. If attacker-supplied data is provided to the Ruby regex compiler, it is possible to extract arbitrary heap data relative to the start of the text, including pointers and sensitive strings. The fixed versions are 3.0.7, 3.1.5, 3.2.4, and 3.3.1.(CVE-2024-27282)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"ruby","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/ruby&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"3.0.3-133.oe2203sp3"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["rubygem-json-2.5.1-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ruby-devel-3.0.3-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ruby-debuginfo-3.0.3-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ruby-debugsource-3.0.3-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","rubygem-openssl-2.2.1-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","rubygem-psych-3.3.2-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","rubygem-io-console-0.5.7-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","ruby-3.0.3-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm","rubygem-bigdecimal-3.0.0-133.oe2203sp3.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["rubygems-devel-3.2.32-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","ruby-help-3.0.3-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-rake-13.0.3-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-rbs-1.4.0-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygems-3.2.32-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-bundler-2.2.32-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-rdoc-6.3.3-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-did_you_mean-1.5.0-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-typeprof-0.15.2-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","ruby-irb-3.0.3-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-rexml-3.2.5-133.oe2203sp3.noarch.rpm","rubygem-minitest-5.14.2-133.oe2203sp3.n